597
00:56:22,300 --> 00:56:23,500
Fräulein Maria?

598
00:56:23,800 --> 00:56:25,700
Can we do this every day?

599
00:56:25,900 --> 00:56:29,100
-Don't you think you'd get tired of it?
-I suppose so.

600
00:56:29,500 --> 00:56:30,800
Every other day?

601
00:56:31,000 --> 00:56:35,600
I haven't had so much fun since we put
glue on Fräulein Josephine's toothbrush.

602
00:56:35,800 --> 00:56:39,700
I can't understand how children
as nice as you can play such tricks.

603
00:56:40,000 --> 00:56:41,800
-It's easy.
-But why do it?

604
00:56:42,000 --> 00:56:44,400
How else can we get
Father's attention?

605
00:56:45,200 --> 00:56:46,800
Oh, I see.

606
00:56:48,200 --> 00:56:50,400
We'll have to think about that one.

607
00:56:52,500 --> 00:56:54,200
All right, over here.

608
00:56:54,400 --> 00:56:55,800
What are we going to do?

609
00:56:56,000 --> 00:56:58,000
Think of a song for the baroness.

610
00:56:58,300 --> 00:57:00,200
Father doesn't like us to sing.

611
00:57:00,500 --> 00:57:03,200
Perhaps we can change his mind.
Now, what songs do you know?

